The paper is about network intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new algorithm for attribute learning using decision trees, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Zero-Shot learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on network intrusion detection, which is a subfield of network and internet security (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes an experimental setup for the evaluation of their approach, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
